Crabs. I gotta do it.

582
00:37:10,919 --> 00:37:12,853
Whatever.

583
00:37:14,189 --> 00:37:16,749
Professor... Tripp.

584
00:37:16,825 --> 00:37:19,419
Hannah, when you get James
back to his apartment...

585
00:37:19,495 --> 00:37:22,055
make sure he's all right
before you leave, okay?

586
00:37:22,131 --> 00:37:24,656
I would if I knew
where I was taking him.

587
00:37:24,733 --> 00:37:27,668
Are you telling me you don't
know where James lives?

588
00:37:27,736 --> 00:37:30,296
Some apartment somewhere.
I've never seen it.

589
00:37:30,372 --> 00:37:33,637
- That strikes me as very odd.
-James is odd.

590
00:37:33,709 --> 00:37:36,234
I know his aunt lives in Sewickley
Heights. I dropped him there once.

591
00:37:36,311 --> 00:37:38,006
Come to think of it,
it wasn't his aunt's house.

592
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,570
He said
she worked there or something.

593
00:37:39,648 --> 00:37:42,913
- I don't remember.
- I need my knapsack.

594
00:37:42,985 --> 00:37:45,112
What's he saying?

595
00:37:45,187 --> 00:37:49,021
His bag. You know that ugly green
thing he's always carrying around?

596
00:37:49,091 --> 00:37:52,060
He must've
left it inside.

597
00:37:52,127 --> 00:37:55,153
Aw, shit. He left it at Thaw.
The auditorium.

598
00:37:55,230 --> 00:37:56,993
- Knapsack!
- All right.

599
00:37:57,066 --> 00:38:00,058
- Let him crash at my house.
- Where should I put him?

600
00:38:00,135 --> 00:38:02,160
In the shape that he's in,
you could stand him up...

601
00:38:02,237 --> 00:38:05,798
in the garage next to the snow
shovels, and he'd be all right.

602
00:38:10,279 --> 00:38:12,747
Grady, if you
wanna talk later...

603
00:38:12,815 --> 00:38:14,749
I'll be up.

604
00:38:22,324 --> 00:38:24,588
Hey, guy! Tripp, the trunk.
You're killing me.

605
00:38:24,660 --> 00:38:28,061
- I'm gonna get it!
- Killin' me!

606
00:38:33,068 --> 00:38:36,697
- [Man ] You drivin' this car?
- Excuse me?

607
00:38:36,772 --> 00:38:39,240
This 1 966 maroon
Ford Galaxy 500.

608
00:38:39,308 --> 00:38:41,435
- You drivin' this car?
- This is my car.

609
00:38:41,510 --> 00:38:44,843
-Bullshit! It 's mine, motherfucker!
-I'm afraid you're mistaken.

610
00:38:44,913 --> 00:38:47,006
- Bullshit!
- Who is that?

611
00:38:47,082 --> 00:38:49,950
Oh, Vernon, go home
to your mother, will you?

612
00:38:50,084 --> 00:38:53,679
- What are you lookin' at?
- I'm lookin' at you, fella.

613
00:38:53,754 --> 00:38:57,246
[ Chuckling ] Hit it, will you?
