614
00:38:57,324 --> 00:39:00,191
- Can we go now, den mother?
- What's with you?

615
00:39:00,260 --> 00:39:01,522
I wonder.

616
00:39:01,595 --> 00:39:03,062
Come on, Crabs.
The kid was comatose.

617
00:39:03,130 --> 00:39:05,564
- Who started that?
- I was trying to calm him down.

618
00:39:05,632 --> 00:39:07,759
Oh, yeah, you calmed him down,
Dr. Feelgood.

619
00:39:07,835 --> 00:39:08,995
[Q]
Grady!

620
00:39:09,069 --> 00:39:11,936
- Hit the brakes!
- Stop the car!

621
00:39:12,005 --> 00:39:15,065
- Stop! Hey!
- What's his problem?

622
00:39:15,142 --> 00:39:18,908
- Back up!
- Get out of the car! Hey!

623
00:39:18,979 --> 00:39:21,106
[ Terry]
Go around, go around him.

624
00:39:21,181 --> 00:39:23,706
- I'm stopping you!
- I don't think so!

625
00:39:23,784 --> 00:39:25,945
[ Whooping ]

626
00:39:26,019 --> 00:39:28,749
Come back here!

627
00:39:28,822 --> 00:39:31,518
- What's this?
- [ Terry] It 's a one- way, guy.

628
00:39:34,761 --> 00:39:37,696
- [ Laughing ]
- [Q] Go, go, go!

629
00:39:40,667 --> 00:39:42,635
[ Terry]
Look out! He 's back!

630
00:39:44,705 --> 00:39:48,266
-Now what?
-[ Terry] You owe him a book too?

631
00:39:48,342 --> 00:39:50,833
You could always
drive over him.

632
00:40:00,521 --> 00:40:03,490
What the hell
was that?

633
00:40:03,557 --> 00:40:05,787
I just got
my hood jumped on.

634
00:40:17,471 --> 00:40:20,668
- Wait here. I'll be right back.
- Where would we go?

635
00:40:20,741 --> 00:40:22,675
[Machine Running]

636
00:40:35,722 --> 00:40:37,656
Hold on a second.

637
00:40:43,697 --> 00:40:45,688
Prof. Tripp.

638
00:40:48,135 --> 00:40:50,399
I guess you're here
for the backpack.

639
00:40:50,470 --> 00:40:52,768
It's Traxler.
Sam.

640
00:40:56,710 --> 00:41:00,305
I saw the manuscript inside,
so when you showed up I figured--

641
00:41:05,219 --> 00:41:08,677
[Grady Narrating]
The Love Parade. So it was true.

642
00:41:08,755 --> 00:41:10,780
The little prick
had finished his book.

643
00:41:10,857 --> 00:41:14,793
- Is it good?
- I don't know. It might be.

644
00:41:20,867 --> 00:41:23,927
[Bell Chiming]

645
00:41:26,740 --> 00:41:28,503
[Narrating]
So there it was.

646
00:41:28,575 --> 00:41:31,567
Somewhere in the night
a Manhattan book editor...

647
00:41:31,645 --> 00:41:34,170
was prowling
the streets of Pittsburgh...

648
00:41:34,248 --> 00:41:36,682
best-selling author
at his side...

649
00:41:36,750 --> 00:41:38,980
dead dog in his trunk.

650
00:41:39,052 --> 00:41:41,418
Say, Prof. Tripp.

651
00:41:41,488 --> 00:41:44,821
Is all that stuff true
about Errol Flynn?

652
00:41:44,891 --> 00:41:47,883
How he used to put paprika
on his dick...

653
00:41:47,961 --> 00:41:52,057
to make it,
you know, like...

654
00:41:52,132 --> 00:41:55,761
more stimulating
for the chick?

655
00:41:58,338 --> 00:42:00,704
Christ, Traxler,
how the hell should I know?

656
00:42:00,774 --> 00:42:03,572
