aren't you?

657
00:42:05,445 --> 00:42:07,379
Oh.

658
00:42:09,316 --> 00:42:13,685
No, it's true. He used to rub
all sorts of things on it.

659
00:42:13,754 --> 00:42:17,383
Salad dressing,
ground lamb.

660
00:42:19,860 --> 00:42:21,794
Sick.

661
00:42:24,398 --> 00:42:27,890
[Narrating] Whenever I wondered
what Sara saw in me...

662
00:42:27,968 --> 00:42:30,368
and I wondered
more than once...

663
00:42:30,437 --> 00:42:33,406
I always came back to the fact
that she loved to read.

664
00:42:33,473 --> 00:42:36,306
She read everything,
every spare moment.

665
00:42:36,376 --> 00:42:39,470
She was a junkie
for the printed word.

666
00:42:39,546 --> 00:42:41,480
And lucky for me...

667
00:42:41,548 --> 00:42:43,880
I manufactured
her drug of choice.

668
00:42:45,419 --> 00:42:47,819
[ Traxler]
ls that your wife?

669
00:42:47,888 --> 00:42:50,482
No, my wife's out of town.

670
00:42:53,794 --> 00:42:56,285
