are we doing here...

671
00:42:56,363 --> 00:42:59,059
Prof. Tripp?

672
00:42:59,132 --> 00:43:01,623
Taking the long way home.

673
00:43:11,678 --> 00:43:14,306
- Take it easy, Prof. Tripp.
- Thanks for the ride.

674
00:45:09,153 --> 00:45:10,711
[Narrating]
I told myself...

675
00:45:10,788 --> 00:45:13,279
I needed to put
everything aside for the moment.

676
00:45:13,357 --> 00:45:15,848
Emily, Sara,
the purloined jacket...

677
00:45:15,927 --> 00:45:18,361
and the dead dog,
and work on my book.

678
00:45:18,429 --> 00:45:20,954
It was started out
as a small book.

679
00:45:24,502 --> 00:45:30,031
Probably about,
oh, 250, 300pages.

680
00:45:30,107 --> 00:45:32,803
[ Dings ]

681
00:45:33,911 --> 00:45:36,709
It had gotten
a little larger in scope.

682
00:45:40,184 --> 00:45:42,652
[ Keys Clattering ]

683
00:45:45,056 --> 00:45:49,117
And the ending,
it kept getting further away.

684
00:45:53,798 --> 00:45:57,234
But the ending was there.
I knew it.

685
00:45:57,301 --> 00:45:59,292
I could almost see it.

686
00:46:06,711 --> 00:46:11,011
[Grady]
James? I'm okay.

687
00:46:11,082 --> 00:46:13,107
I just lost my balance.

688
00:46:13,184 --> 00:46:15,482
