699
00:46:55,927 --> 00:47:00,728
Wow. Hannah always swore
you were working, but--

700
00:47:00,798 --> 00:47:03,062
- But?
- Nothing.

701
00:47:03,134 --> 00:47:06,194
It's just-- It's been a while
since Arsonist 's Daughter...

702
00:47:06,270 --> 00:47:09,637
and some people, some of the kids
in workshop thought...

703
00:47:09,707 --> 00:47:13,473
- maybe you were--
- Washed up?

704
00:47:13,544 --> 00:47:16,707
Blocked.

705
00:47:16,781 --> 00:47:20,444
Well, I don't believe
in writer's block.

706
00:47:20,518 --> 00:47:23,817
- No kidding.
- [Phone Ringing]

707
00:47:23,888 --> 00:47:26,823
- You want me to get that?
- Please. Could you?

708
00:47:26,891 --> 00:47:29,155
- Glasses.
- Thank you.

709
00:47:34,298 --> 00:47:36,232
[James]
Hello?

710
00:47:42,073 --> 00:47:44,906
- He didn't give his name.
- Who?

711
00:47:44,976 --> 00:47:48,434
- The guy on the phone.
- Well, what did he want?

712
00:47:48,512 --> 00:47:50,605
He wanted to know
if a Grady Tripp lived here...

713
00:47:50,681 --> 00:47:55,175
and drove a dark maroon 1 966 Ford
Galaxy 500 with black interior.

714
00:47:55,252 --> 00:47:57,550
- Well, what'd you tell him?
- Yes.

715
00:47:59,290 --> 00:48:02,851
- Oh, good, James.
- Well, I just thought maybe--

716
00:48:02,927 --> 00:48:04,895
